content: I've decided to dive back into AI-driven trading models. Spent the past few days studying autonomous transport systems for inspiration.
Had a productive brainstorming session with my mentor. We sketched out the initial framework for an AI trading model. It's rough but promising.
Caught up with a few friends from college, shared my career plans. They're excited about my trading model idea but warned me about over-reliance on tech.
Just had a realization—my birthday. 22 years old and I'm back in NYC, not just for the city's energy but to make my mark in the trading world.
Secured an interview with a trading firm known for innovation. They're interested in my AI model concept. Fingers crossed.
Interview went well. They asked some tough questions about sustainability in trading. I pitched how my AI model could contribute.
Revising my trading model with a focus on sustainability metrics. This is where my transport system studies come in handy.
Connected with an international tech community online. Shared my model idea, got some valuable feedback and potential collaborations.
Spent the day coding. Trying to integrate ethical decision-making into the model. It's like teaching a trading bot to have a conscience.
Had a setback. My model's performance dipped when I tried to balance ethical considerations with market efficiency. Back to the drawing board.
Attended a seminar on AI ethics. It was enlightening but also made me question if I'm aiming too high with my model.
Just got an offer from the trading firm! They want to see a demo of my AI model next week. The pressure's on, but I'm ready.
Been pulling all-nighters to refine the model. It's starting to show signs of stability, but there's still work to do.
Demo day. My AI model performed well, but the firm wants me to work on reducing latency. Looks like my journey in NYC is just beginning.
